name: Initiating and responding tribunal of State
text: §576B-203  Initiating and responding tribunal of State.  Under this chapter, a tribunal of this State may serve as an initiating tribunal to forward proceedings to a tribunal of another state, and as a responding tribunal for proceedings initiated in another state or a foreign country. [L 1997, c 295, pt of §1; am L 2015, c 77, pt of §1]
